1957;;The Tommy Steele Story;;British;;Gerard Bryant;;Tommy Steele, Patrick Westwood;;musical;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Tommy_Steele_Story;;Tommy Steele lives with his mother and father in their London home. He works with a bellboy until he injures his spine doing judo. In hospital he is given a guitar to help with his therapy and he starts to play to entertain patients and staff. He works on an ocean liner, performing in his spare time, and gets a job playing in a coffee bar. He is popular with audiences and gets a recording contract.